{"id":2442,"date":"2013-04-26T09:12:08","date_gmt":"2013-04-26T14:12:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/lionsgate_logo_intro.php"},"modified":"2013-04-26T09:12:08","modified_gmt":"2013-04-26T14:12:08","slug":"lionsgate_logo_intro","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/lionsgate_logo_intro.php","title":{"rendered":"Lionsgate (Logo Intro)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/lionsgate_logo.jpg\" alt=\"Lionsgate Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>About: <\/strong> (Est. 1995) &#8220;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.lionsgate.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Lionsgate<\/a> is a leading global entertainment company with a strong and diversified presence in motion picture production and distribution, television programming and syndication, home entertainment, family entertainment, digital distribution, new channel platforms and international distribution and sales.  Led by THE HUNGER GAMES and THE TWILIGHT SAGA young adult franchises, the Company&#8217;s feature film slate generated more than $1.2 billion at the domestic box office and $2.5 billion worldwide in 2012.  Lionsgate&#8217;s television business includes 28 shows on 20 different networks, including such iconic brands as MAD MEN, WEEDS, ANGER MANAGEMENT and NASHVILLE on ABC.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Design by:<\/strong> <a href=\"http:\/\/www.devastudios.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Deva Studios<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Ed.&#8217;s Notes:<\/strong> A little too close to Universal? Before and after intro movies below (or after the jump).<\/p>\n<p><strong>Relevant links:<\/strong> <a href=\"http:\/\/www.devastudios.com\/works\/lionsgate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Deva Studios case study<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Select quote:<\/strong> &#8220;The new design features a light-speed journey through the galaxy, reflecting the vast universe of creativity that exists within Lionsgate. The animation is replete with visual reference to the branding heritage of the studio. Sharp eyed viewers will spot a lion constellation in the galaxy, and note that the logo resolves in a cloudscape that draws its visual DNA from the previous incarnation of the logo (also designed by Devastudios).&#8221;<\/p><!--more--><p><iframe width=\"574\" height=\"323\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/NX4rMOsFJWE\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">&#8220;Before&#8221; intro.<\/p>\n<p><iframe width=\"574\" height=\"323\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/XtxzYu0itFU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">&#8220;After&#8221; intro.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.BrianJCrowley.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Brian J. Crowley<\/a> for the tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_130426_b_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_130426_b_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"574\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gif\" alt=\"Voting Begins\" \/>\n<table class=\"table\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\t<tr valign=\"top\">\n        <!--VOTE CONCEPT-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t\t<div id = \"pollDiv1\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/td>\n